SIMPLE: unkind
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unkind
<hw>Un*kind"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Kin</er>
kindred.]</ety> <def>Having no race or kindred; childless.</def>
<mark>[Obs. & R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unkind</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unkind
<hw>Un*kind"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not kind; contrary to
nature, or the law of kind or kindred; unnatural.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Such <xex>unkind</xex> abominations.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Wanting in kindness, sympathy, benevolence,
gratitude, or the like; cruel; harsh; unjust; ungrateful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He is <qex>unkind</qex> that recompenseth not; but he is most
<qex>unkind</qex> that forgetteth.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Elyot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*kind"ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*kind"ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unkindliness</ent>⟦br⟧
